generating a database entry at said node based on said transcoding information contained on said header; 
generating a tag pointing to said database entry of said transcoding information contained on said header of said portion of data; 
correlating said tag pointing to said database entry with said portion of data; and 
transcoding the portion of data based on said transcoding information of said database pointed to by said tag without requiring access to said header or other data within said portion of data.

1. A method for reducing an acoustic echo in audio signals transmitted between a first location and a second location over a communication system, the method comprising: 
receiving a first digital signal and/or a second digital signal, the first digital signal encodes sounds produced at the first location and the second digital signal encodes an acoustic echo and sounds produced at the second location; 
computing a control state identifying the signals as being output from the first location and/or the second location; 
computing an approximate acoustic echo of the acoustic echo detected at the second location based on the control state; 
subtracting the approximate acoustic echo from the second digital signal to produce an output digital signal; and 
transmitting the output digital signal to the first location.

